name: Alam Baru Camp Bali
address: Pondok Sidem, Banjar Penginyahan, Puhu, Payangan, Gianyar Regency, Bali 80572, Indonesia
review 1: Excellent camp beautiful scenery and the owner is so lovely. Helped us so much when we came in the night (never do that always come in the day haha)
review 2: Very good. Kind of hard to find. They need to have signs for the location.  Spectacular views. Very nice rice fields. Definitely recommended!
review 3:
Good view, if you want to feel in the middle of nowhere come here for a while and look around, and boom. U will feel it.
For people who hate being exposed better you come on weekdays or avoid Balinese holidays.
Peaceful place sometimes
review 4: Incredible experiences! Fresh air, place to connect with mother earth, referch our mind-body-soul
